Accident Release Prevention Program

The accident release prevention program features containment for the one-ton chlorine containers and double containment piping for the liquid chlorine.  The chlorine system is designed to shut down automatically if there is a leak in any section of the distribution system.  Additional safety systems include: 
? An automatic closing valve (electric powered, fail closed) that activates when a chlorine leak is detected, or in the event of a power failure for both of the one-ton container containment vessels; 
? A seismic detector to automatically activate the chlorine valve closure system when an earthquake exceeds a set threshold, whether or not a leak is detected; 
? Chlorine sensors in the storage area, evaporator room, process area, process vessel ventilation ducts, and scrubber exhaust stack; 
? Chlorine alarms (visual and audible) inside and outside the evaporator building; 
? Fenceline monitoring for chlorine;
? A central chlorine alarm monitoring station;
? Personal protective equipment (breathing apparatus) for chlorine handlers;
? Training for system operators;
? Written operating procedures;
? An emergency response plan; and,
? An emergency back-up electrical generator for power to critical systems, including the chlorine monitoring system. 

